4-AcO-DMT (4-acetoxy-N,N-dimethyltryptamine), also known as psilacetin, is a synthetic psychedelic drug in the tryptamine family that acts as a prodrug for the compound psilocin. It is chemically related to psilocybin and produces effects similar to magic mushrooms, but is sometimes reported to cause fewer gastrointestinal side effects
